      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand your concerns, but it's always better to err on the side of caution. That being said, I'm not saying you should go to the hospital, but if you're feeling like your chest is truly constricted, it's possible that you're experiencing something more serious. However, if you're feeling anxious, try some relaxation techniques like progressive muscle relaxation, visualization, or a warm bath. You can also try taking a few deep breaths in through your nose and out through your mouth, focusing on the sensation of the breath moving in and out of your body. If you're still feeling unwell after 30 minutes, consider reaching out to a telemedicine service or a trusted friend or family member for support.",
